caption.body: The 049 Constellation was an extremely fast, highly advanced, and revolutionary large-capacity airliner with a unique dolphin-shaped fuselage and distinctive tripletail. Learn more about TWA and Constellation in our ”Queen of the Skies: The Legacy of the Lockheed Constellation” exhibition. “Queen of the Skies” is on display pre-security, in the Aviation Museum and Library in the International Terminal. The Aviation Museum and Library is open from Sunday through Friday, 10am to 4:30pm.  #TWASkyliner  TWA (Trans World Airlines) Lockheed Constellation San Francisco poster   Early 1950s SFO Museum Collection 1995.55.01
